Package io.github.ericmedvet.jnb.datastructure

package io.github.ericmedvet.jnb.datastructure
Provides interfaces and classes for modeling a few data structures (e.g., Grid, Table) and useful concepts (e.g., NamedFunction, Parametrized).
  • Class
    Description
    AbstractGrid<T>
    A partly abstract implementation of Grid.
    ArrayGrid<T>
    An implementation of Grid which internally stores the elements with an array.
    DoubleRange
    An interval delimited by two bounds, min and max.
    FormattedFunction<T,R>
    A function which can format its output according to a format.
    FormattedNamedFunction<T,R>
    A function with a name which can format its output according to a format.
    Grid<T>
    An object that maps bi-dimensional integer coordinates defined in a finite domain to values, as in a grid like structure.
    Grid.Entry<V>
    A grid entry, i.e., a pair of a coordinate key and a value value describing a cell of the grid.
    Grid.Key
    A coordinate of a grid, defined by two ints x and y.
    GridUtils
    This class consists of static utility methods for operating on grids, i.e., objects of type Grid.
    HashMapGrid<T>
    An implementation of Grid which internally stores the elements with an HashMap where keys are grid coordinates.
    HashMapTable<R,C,T>
    A table that internally stores its values in an HashMap.
    NamedFunction<T,R>
    A function with a name.
    NumericalParametrized<T extends NumericalParametrized<T>>
    An object which has a modifiable parameter of type double[], i.e., parametrized with numerical parameters.
    Pair<F,S>
    A pair of two elements of (in general) different types.
    Parametrized<T extends Parametrized<T,P>,P>
    An object which has a modifiable parameter of type P.
    Table<R,C,T>
    An object that stores elements of type T in a modifiable table like structure where cells are indexed through pairs of coordinates R,C.
    Table.Series<P,S,T>
    A series of values of tells, representing either a row or a column.
    Table.Unmodifiable<R,C,T>
    A read-only table for which all the methods for modifying the content throw an UnsupportedOperationException.
    TriConsumer<I1,I2,I3>
    An operation that accepts three input arguments and returns no result.
    TriFunction<I1,I2,I3,O>
    A function that accepts two arguments and produces a result.
